#sponsored 🚨Recipe below🚨 Add some sparkle to your next mug of hot cocoa with ✨Peppermint Whipped Cream✨ using @kempscows Select Heavy Whipping Cream! My boys went CRAZY for this homemade whipped cream, and I love that it's made with just 3️⃣ everyday ingredients. Kemps has been providing Midwestern families with fresh dairy from community farmers since 1914, and their heavy whipping cream whips up beautifully into this hot cocoa topping. 😋

Fun and festive for the holidays, and all season (that shall not be named) long! ❄️

🍬Peppermint Whipped Cream🍬

Ingredients:
2 cups Kemps Select Heavy Whipping Cream
1/2 cup + 2 Tablespoons powdered sugar
2 teaspoons peppermint extract

Directions: 
1) Chill the bowl of an electric mixer and the whisk attachment, or a large mixing bowl and the beaters if using a hand held mixer, for at least 10 minutes in the freezer. Additionally, ensure your heavy whipping cream is very cold. 
2) Add heavy whipping cream to the chilled bowl then beat on low speed while sprinkling in powdered sugar. Turn the heat up to medium then, once the whipped cream begins to thicken, turn the speed up to high and beat until stiff peaks have formed. The entire process will take 6-7 minutes. Add peppermint extract then beat briefly to incorporate. Dollop onto hot chocolate or coffee (or whatever you want!) Store leftover whipped cream in the refrigerator for 2-3 days. 

#milkmakesitmerrier

#ad ✨Stone Fruit Caprese Salad ✨with fresh produce from @hyvee !
 
I love getting my produce from Hy-Vee because they source from only the best, expert growers to provide a wide selection of fresh, quality produce that shine in this summer salad. It’s perfect for pairing with a grilled dinner, or served all on its own. Elegant and gorgeous, but a cinch to make, as you can see! 
 
Trust me when I tell you that adding sweet peaches, nectarines, and cherries to the classic Caprese combo of tomatoes, mozzarella cheese, and basil is a TOTAL upgrade. 
 
Have you ever tried a sweet spin on Caprese Salad? Click the link in my bio to shop for the ingredients from Hy-Vee! 
 
✨Stone Fruit Caprese Salad ✨ 
 
serves 2-4 
 
Ingredients: 
2 yellow peaches, sliced 
2 nectarines, sliced 
2 vine-ripened tomatoes, sliced 
8oz fresh mozzarella cheese ball, sliced 
1 cup sweet cherries, pitted 
balsamic reduction 
extra virgin olive oil 
salt 
 
Directions: 
Layer the peach, nectarine, tomato, and mozzarella cheese slices on a platter. Dot with cherries then drizzle with balsamic reduction, extra virgin olive oil, and salt then serve. 
 
#HyVeeProduce #salad #summersalad #glutenfree

#ad Pickle Wraps are a Midwest picnic and potluck staple, so trust me when I tell you that turning them into a high-protein dip using @kempscows cottage cheese is a total upgrade!

Equal parts creamy, crunchy, savory, and zesty, this flavor-packed dip is not only gluten free, but packed with protein too. Serve with crackers or crudite.

You can find #kemps products throughout Iowa, Minnesota, Wisconsin, and Illinois. Will you give this chip-busting dip a try?

Pickle Wrap Dip

Ingredients:
1 cup Kemps 2% cottage cheese
1 Tablespoon pickle juice
1/2 teaspoon onion powder
1/2 teaspoon garlic powder
1 cup minced dill pickles
1 cup gluten free corned beef OR salami OR ham, chopped

Directions:
Add cottage cheese, pickle juice, onion powder, and garlic powder to the bowl of a food processor then process until very smooth, scraping down the sides as needed. Scoop cottage cheese into a mixing bowl then add chopped dill pickles and corned beef. Serve
with crackers or crudite.

My take on the ✨Viral Cottage Cheese Pizza Bowl✨

😍 I’ve been making high-protein, low-carb cottage cheese pizza/lasagna bowls for lunch on repeat (they’re not winning any beauty awards but legit taste like the real thing and keep me so full).

🙏🏻 What I’ve been missing though is some TEXTURE + veggies/fiber/nutrients. 

💡 The solution? Add roasted spaghetti squash! I could eat this every single day. Truly. I eyeball all the ingredient measurements but here’s a general idea. You can’t screw this up so don’t overthink it!

✨Cottage Cheese Pizza Bowl with Texture✨

Serves 1

Ingredients:
1/4 - 1/2 cup cottage cheese
1/4 cup marinara/pizza sauce
1 cup roasted spaghetti squash
Pizza toppings: I like sliced black olives and pepperoni
pinch dried Italian seasoning

Directions: 
1️⃣ Add cottage cheese, marinara/pizza sauce, and spaghetti squash to a bowl then cover with a paper towel and microwave for 1-1/2 minutes, stirring halfway through. 
2️⃣ Top with desired pizza toppings and dried Italian seasoning then microwave for another 30 seconds. 
3️⃣ DEVOUR then come back and tell me how much you loved this easy lunch recipe!!!

#glutenfree #highprotein #lowcarb #easyrecipes #lunchideas #celiac #cottagecheese

#sponsored 🎅🏼 Santa called and said all he wants for Christmas is Gluten Free Chocolate Crinkle Cookies with @cameronscoffee White Chocolate Peppermint Coffee! 🍫☕️

Cameron’s Coffee brings smooth, never bitter, coffee-shop-quality products to your home, and their holiday flavors are a lovely way to treat yourself this time of year. Brew up morning or night — GF Chocolate Crinkle Cookie on the side is optional, but encouraged. 😜

Find the cookie recipe below + 10 more #glutenfree Christmas cookies and treats by clicking on the link in my profile @iowagirleats 

Visit www.CameronsCoffee.com to learn more and find a store near you that carries their festive holiday blends!

✨Gluten Free Chocolate Crinkle Cookies✨
 
Ingredients:
1 cup granulated sugar
1/4 cup vegetable oil
2 eggs
1 teaspoon vanilla extract
1 cup gluten free measure for measure flour
1/2 cup unsweetened cocoa powder
1 teaspoon baking powder
1/4 teaspoon salt
1 cup powdered sugar

Directions: 
1️⃣ Add the sugar and oil to the bowl of an electric mixer, or a large mixing bowl if using a hand held mixer, then mix on medium speed until combined. 
2️⃣ Add the eggs one at a time, mixing on medium speed until just combined before adding the next egg. Add the vanilla extract then mix on low until just combined. 
3️⃣ Add the GF flour, cocoa powder, baking powder, and salt to a medium-size mixing bowl then whisk to combine. Add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients in 2 batches, mixing on medium speed until just combined before adding the second batch. Use a spatula to give the dough a good stir then cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours or up to 48 hours. 
4️⃣ Preheat the oven to 350 degrees, line a half sheet pan with parchment paper, then add the powdered sugar to a bowl. Scoop out 1 Tablespoon of the chilled dough at a time then roll between your hands to create a ball and roll in the powdered sugar. Bake for 8-10 minutes then rap the baking sheet on the counter to slightly deflate the cookies. After 2 minutes, move the cookies to a cooling rack to cool.


#CameronsCoffee #AlwaysSmoothNeverBitter #glutenfreebaking
